Package projects.pqueue.lists

Class StaticArrayList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.pqueue.lists.StaticArrayList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type held by the ArrayLinearList.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, List<T>
    public class StaticArrayList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements List<T>

    StaticArrayList is an implementation of a List with an array. It does not make any practical sense, because it would be much more efficient to use a LinkedList in the general case, but it is possible theoretically. The only method of the List interface that is executed more efficiently in StaticArrayList than in LinkedList is delete(int) which runs in O(1). Of course, other methods such as pushFront(Object) are horribly inneficient.

    You should not edit this class! It is given to you as a resource for your project.

    See Also:
    LinkedList, DoublyLinkedList

        public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object other)
        Standard equals() method. Two LinearLists are equal if they contain the exact same elements at the same positions. Note that this equals() method allows for comparing an ArrayLinearList with an ArrayListLinearList, and potentially allowing them to be equal because they maintain the aforementioned contract! We are interested in ADT comparison, not 1-1 memory allocation comparison.
